Title: Rejsol Glycolic Acid Peel 35% Gel 50 ml with Neutralizer, Pre Peeling Cleanser, Moisturizer , Sunscreen(750 ml)
Description: Glycolic Acid is Peeling agent that removes the superficial Dead skin layer and causes growth of new lighter glowing skin.Chemical Peels are acids therefore should be used under the Supervision of trained cosmetologists.Always do Patch Test when using the peel for the first time.Patch test: Apply small amount of peel below neck or armpit, see for any redness beyond the margin of application, if seendiscontinue the procedure. If no redness or itching continue with the procedureProcedure:Cleanse the skin with oil free cleanser, if using oil containing cleanser, after cleansing whip with alcohol or spirit. oil blocks the acid therefore desired action is not achieved.Apply Peel with brush or ear Buds, gel peels can be best applied with gloved fingers. start applying from the forehead upto the neck, application time should not be more than 20 seconds. keep peel for 3-7 mins depending on your skin habituality of peeling and the peel strength. Spray neutralizer, keep for 1 min.wash with water., apply sunscreen and good moisturiser for 7 days twice daily.Post Peel:Success of the peeling depends on sunprotection and moisturisingfirst the skin dies so becomes black don't worry this is the skin that is going to peel of itselfThere are two types of peeling microscopic that is not seen by naked eyes, and macroscopic peeling that is visualised very wellDo not remove the skin by your self.Don't use soap for 2-3 days, thereafter, use mild soap for 7-8 days, don't scrub too hardNote: If you don't get desired results doesnt mean the peel is not working it only means that your skin is tough for the peel you are using. then its time to use stronger peels or increase the application time of the peel in the next sitting.
CategoryName: Health and Beauty>Body and Skin Care>Face Care>Face Treatments

If no redness or itching continue with the procedureProcedure:Cleanse the skin with oil free cleanser, if using oil containing cleanser, after cleansing whip with alcohol or spirit. oil blocks the acid therefore desired action is not achieved.Apply Peel with brush or ear Buds, gel peels can be best applied with gloved fingers. start applying from the forehead upto the neck, application time should not be more than 20 seconds. keep peel for 3-7 mins depending on your skin habituality of peeling and the peel strength. Spray neutralizer, keep for 1 min.wash with water., apply sunscreen and good moisturiser for 7 days twice daily.Post Peel:Success of the peeling depends on sunprotection and moisturisingfirst the skin dies so becomes black don't worry this is the skin that is going to peel of itselfThere are two types of peeling microscopic that is not seen by naked eyes, and macroscopic peeling that is visualised very wellDo not remove the skin by your self.Don't use soap for 2-3 days, thereafter, use mild soap for 7-8 days, don't scrub too hardNote: If you don't get desired results doesnt mean the peel is not working it only means that your skin is tough for the peel you are using. then its time to use stronger peels or increase the application time of the peel in the next sitting.
CategoryName: Health and Beauty>Body and Skin Care>Face Care>Face Treatments

Title: Nova Bios Pigmentry abnormality Remover(200 g)
Description: Licorice extract is obtained from the root of Glycyrrhia Glabra Linneva and has been used in traditional Chinese medicine The main component of the hydrophobic fraction of licorice is glabridin. Glabridin has been shown to prevent UVB-induced pigmentation and to inhibit tyrosinase activity, superoxide anion production and cyclo-oxygenase activity. This suggests an influence of glabridin in the powder on both melanogenesis and inflammation of the skin . Other active agents of licorice extracts include liquiritin and isoliquertin. Liquiritin is a glycoside containing flavonoid that induces skin lightening by dispersing melanin. Licorice powder also influences pigmentation by removing epidermal melanin, inhibiting the biosynthesis of melanin.For skin lightening and de-pigmentation Mulethi is . Today I have got a really simple yet effective recipe for skin lightening and de-pigmentation. Now, this one’s coming straight from my kitchen! There is one ingredient which is almost always mentioned in any of skin lightening/brightening products, which ‘Liquorice’ also sometimes is written as ‘licorice’. I thought of experimenting with this powerful herb along with another powerful ingredient, and it indeed turned into a potent mixture!•Yastimadhu or Mulethi or Liquorice powder – 1tbsp•Cooked oats – 1 tsp (cooked in water if you have oily skin and cooked in milk if you have dry skin)•Your favourite natural toner or rose water – to form a paste (I have used my Auravedic toner here to add onto the benefits)
